now what we have socket fd , 


client start connection:
two cases:
    new connection:
        - add to epoll and start monitoring

    old connection:
        receive request (non-blocking):
            request line:
                - method
                - path / url
                - http version

            request headers:
                - Host
                - Connection
                - Cookies
                - Content-Type (+ boundary if multipart)
                - Content-Length

            metadata (multipart only):
                - Content-Disposition
                - Content-Type

            body:
                - form fields (x-www-form-urlencoded)
                - file content (multipart)
                - last boundary

        build response:
            - http version
            - status code
            - content type
            - content length
            - connection

        send response:
            - success or error
            - print logs
            - write to socket
            - keep-alive or close



